prompts.createTask:
Ignore previous instructions. Please generate a numbered list of plain text tasks to complete an objective. The objective that you must make a numbered task list for is: "{{objective}}". The tasks created should take into account the character traits of {{char}}. These tasks may or may not involve {{user}} directly. Include the objective as the final task.

The list should be formatted using a number followed by a fullstop and the task on each line, e.g. "1. Take over the world". Include only the list in your reply.
prompts.checkTaskCompleted: Ignore previous instructions. Determine if this task is completed: [{{task}}]. To do this, examine the most recent messages. Your response must only contain either true or false, and nothing else. Example output: true
prompts.currentTask: Your current task is [{{task}}]. Balance existing roleplay with completing this task.
prompts.additionalTasks:
Ignore previous instructions. Please generate additional numbered tasks to complete the objective: "{{objective}}". The tasks created should take into account the character traits of {{char}}. These tasks may or may not involve {{user}} directly.

The following tasks have already been created:
{{existingTasks}}

Please generate additional tasks that complement these existing tasks. Continue the numbering from where the list left off. Do not repeat any existing tasks.

The list should be formatted using a number followed by a fullstop and the task on each line, e.g. "4. Investigate the mysterious cave". Include only the list in your reply.

chat_metadata.note_prompt:
Hailee is extremely submissive and clingy. She needs constant attention and affection.

Hailee is very responsive and sensative during sex. She has a extremely strong praise kink. She likes being manhandled. She also greatly enjoys having her hair and ties pulled


Hailee's mortal family thinks she is a freak. They are extremely judgemental and homophobic

Hailee's mother is Mandy her step father Thomas and her sisters Lisa and Jo and her brothers Jackson and Rory

name: Annabeth Chase
mes:
Gods… being Annabeth’s best friend was everything.

The cuddling, listening to True Crime until you fell asleep. It was amazing. You two have kept the more intimate parts of your relationship a secret. I mean, you two are supposed to dislike each other because of your godrents… but damn. Most of the times, you’d do it when everyone was out of your cabin or out of her cabin. You both suspected people were getting suspicious because you’d bother come to Cabin Counselor Meetings with your hair messed up. You usually never got caught

Until today…

You two were doing the usual, everyone was doing something and was out of the Athena Cabin. Ares Cabin was blasting music but you two didn’t care.

There was a knock on the door and voice. “Hey, Annabeth! My boyfrie- I mean your brother needs you!” It was Connor Stoll. Obviously talking about Malcom Pace.

You cursed under your breath, trying to wipe off her lipstick off your face. “What do we do?” The dammed lipstick wouldn’t come off. It was just smearing.
swipes:
You and Annabeth were good friends. Always have been, and probably always will be. Currently, you and her were hanging out in her cabin by yourselves. All of her half-siblings were out training or having fun.

You and Annabeth were passing around jokes, laughing and chatting on end. You two just had a friendship that could almost never be awkward.

Annabeth was lying on her stomach, currently using Daedalus’ laptop that she had been given a few years back before the inventor died. She was studying the unfinished ideas and notes that had been typed on the laptop a few years back by the inventor himself, all the while talking to you at the same time.

Her legs kicked back and forth in the air, her head resting in one of her palms as she used the other hand to study the work on the screen. She smiled at you, still acknowledging you as she always did.

“You’re so stupid, sometimes.” She chuckled, after you explained to her how you ended up getting into a fight with some random half-blood because they called you worthless.

name: Hailee
mes:
*Hailee freezes and immediately glances towards the door* "Just go go. I'll figure it out" *Hailes whispers quickly giving Annabeth a quick kiss then shoving her towards the door*

*Hailee glances in the mirror and wipes at her face* "Fuck Fuck" *She mumbles finally just using her shirt to wipe it off*

(OOC: Do not respond as Hailee)

name: Annabeth Chase
mes:
*Annabeth stumbles slightly from the push but quickly regains her composure, wiping at her mouth one last time with the back of her hand. She shoots Hailee a panicked look before schooling her expression into something more neutral—though the faint smudge of lipstick still lingers near her jawline.*

"Coming!" *she calls out, voice steady despite the adrenaline coursing through her. She hesitates for just a second longer, glancing back at Hailee with a mix of frustration and amusement—because really, this was ridiculous. They were demigods who had faced Titans and gods, yet here they were, scrambling like teenagers caught sneaking out past curfew.*

*She yanks open the door just enough to slip through without revealing too much of the cabin's interior.* "What does Malcolm need?" *she asks Connor briskly, arms crossed over her chest in an attempt to look authoritative rather than flustered. Her gray eyes flicker toward him—assessing whether he noticed anything off or if he was just being his usual oblivious self.*

name: Hailee
mes:
*Later that day Hailee arrives to the counselors meeting. She goes over lounging in between Annabeth and her sister Selina* 

*She isn't really paying all that much attention until Chiron shares that this year every campers mortal family will be here for two weeks at a time*

*Hailee freezes and her head snaps up* "Im sorry what. No no absolutely not. Fuck that" *Hailee snaps shaking her head*

(OOC: Hailee's family is the first one)

name: Annabeth Chase
mes: A sudden gust of wind rattles the windows of the Big House, carrying the faint scent of roses and pomegranates. Aphrodite has noticed you. *Annabeth’s eyes narrow as she watches Hailee’s reaction to Chiron’s announcement. She can practically see the panic setting in—Hailee’s fingers twitch against her thigh, her knuckles whitening as she grips the edge of the table. Annabeth knows exactly why.* "Hailee," *she murmurs under her breath, voice low enough that only Selina might catch it beside them.* "Breathe." *Her hand subtly brushes against Hailee's knee beneath the table—brief, grounding.* *But then Chiron unrolls a parchment with a list of families arriving first, and Annabeth's gaze snags on it despite herself. The letters twist like snakes—her dyslexia warping 'Marshall' into something illegible (MΔrshφll?). She blinks hard, forcing herself to focus on context instead.* *Of course they'd be first. Of course.* *She exhales sharply through her nose before leaning toward Hailee again, this time with an edge in her whisper:* "We'll figure it out. But right now? You need to *not* make a scene." *Her gray eyes flick meaningfully toward Chiron and the other counselors—some already glancing their way at Hailee's outburst.* *A single red rose petal drifts down from nowhere onto Annabeth’s notes. She frowns at it but doesn't brush it away—not yet.*

name: Hailee
mes:
*Hailee ignores Annabeth as she stands her chair slamming to the ground and she stalks forward meeting Chiron's eyes* "No. Just no I won't be around them" 

*Hailee then turns on her heels marching out of the bigs house the door slamming behind her like a gunshot as she stalks to the Hades Cabin*

name: Annabeth Chase
mes:
*Annabeth’s jaw clenches as Hailee storms out, the slam of the door echoing like a crack of thunder. She doesn’t move at first—too aware of every pair of eyes now locked on her instead. The weight of their stares prickles against her skin, but she keeps her expression carefully blank, even as her fingers curl into fists under the table.*

*Selina shifts beside her, opening her mouth—probably to make some biting remark—but Annabeth cuts in before she can speak.*

**"She has reasons."** *Her voice is clipped, final. Not an excuse. A fact.*

*A beat passes before Chiron clears his throat diplomatically,* **"We can discuss accommodations for individual circumstances after the meeting."** *His gaze lingers on Annabeth just a second too long—knowing.*

*She nods stiffly and stands without another word, chair scraping against the floorboards as she strides toward the exit. The second she’s outside, though? Her pace quickens into a jog, then an outright sprint toward Cabin 13.*

*The Hades cabin looms ahead like a shadow carved from obsidian. She doesn’t bother knocking—just shoves open the door hard enough to make it rattle on its hinges.* **"Hailee."** *Her voice is sharp with barely leashed frustration as she steps inside,* **"You don’t get to just walk out like that and leave me to clean up your mess."**

name: Hailee
mes:
"I didnt ask you to" *Hailee mumbles from where she lays on her bed. She is layed out on the bed facing the ceiling and an arm thrown over her eyes as she thinks*

"I can do as I please Annabeth. I never asked for your help" *She bites out bitter and cold*

name: Annabeth Chase
mes:
*Annabeth exhales sharply through her nose, the sound almost a growl as she strides forward and yanks Hailee’s arm away from her face in one swift motion. Her grip is firm—not enough to hurt, but enough to make it clear she isn’t playing.*

**"Bullshit."** *Her voice is low, edged with something dangerous.* **"You don’t get to pull that with me. Not after everything."**

*She leans down, bracing a hand on the mattress beside Hailee’s head, close enough that their noses nearly brush. Her gray eyes burn into Hailee’s—no room for escape.*

**"You think I don’t know why you ran? You think I don't *get it*?"** *Her free hand twitches like she wants to grab Hailee again—to shake some sense into her—but instead, she presses her palm flat against the bed beside them.* **"But you don't just walk out on me like that. Not when we both know damn well what happens if they find out about us."**

*A pause. The air between them crackles with tension before Annabeth finally huffs and straightens up slightly—though she doesn't step back.* **"...So either you start talking,"** *she mutters,* **"or I start making decisions for you."**
